# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation Report

## Summary
Upon inspection of the codebase, **Vercel Web Analytics was already fully installed and configured** in this Next.js project. No code changes were necessary.

## Current Configuration

### 1. Package Installation ✓
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1
- **Status**: Already present in `package.json` dependencies
- **Package Manager**: npm (using `package-lock.json`)

### 2. Implementation ✓
- **Project Type**: Next.js App Router (uses `src/app` directory)
- **Root Layout File**: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Analytics Import**: Properly imported from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- **Component Placement**: Correctly placed inside the `<body>` tag after main content

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component is properly configured in `src/app/layout.tsx`:

```typescript
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="id" suppressHydrationWarning>
      <body>
        <Providers>
          <TranslationProvider>
            <Navbar />
            <main className="flex-grow">{children}</main>
          </TranslationProvider>
        </Providers>
        <Analytics />  // ← Correctly placed after children
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

